@startuml
title PB-428 UC12 View fund details

actor "Next Customer" as NextCustomer
participant Core_Next #lightgray { } 
database Next_Database #white { } 

rectangle Abstract [==Abstract: This use case will return fund details for a single fund.  ==]


note right of NextCustomer : The App will make a call to \nCore Next to get all the\ndetails for a fund.\nIt will pass required input:\n - Fund ID\n 


nextcustomer -> core_next : HTTP GET /investments/funds/completeDetails



ref over next_customer,core_bradesco[Use existing methodology to get complete details for a fund.]




box "" ##White

    participant Core_Bradesco{ } 

end box ' end group

' note left of abstract : Use Case Description :\nThe app makes an API request using http method Get on endpoint investments/fund/details/{fund_id} .The response contains information about funds like name , description etc.. It also includes new fields such as risk score which was not present before this change but now added into product table so we can fetch them from there instead making another api calls just because some data wasn't available earlier due lack thereof requirement at time development started working towards adding these features later down line after initial release went live successfully without any major issues reported back yet still needs improvement though since more work remains ahead especially regarding performance optimization where necessary given current state things stand today vis-a-vis future goals set forth by stakeholders involved here including yourself dear reader who happens upon reading my words written above thus far... hope you find value in what I've shared below! :)  

@enduml
